item.title: Philippians 3:12-14
item.description: In this passage, Paul explains why he is content but not complacent. Paul sometimes compared the rigors of athletic training to Christian growth and development challenges. He believed Christians should never become complacent with where they were in their spiritual development. Growth is the natural desire of the mature Christian. Feed: https://podpoint.com/feed/5637
